## Part 2: Telegram Bundled Plugin Structure

### Directory Contents:

**Root Files:**
- `index.ts` - Entry point exporting plugin definition
- `package.json` - NPM metadata with OpenClaw plugin config
- `openclaw.plugin.json` - Plugin manifest
- `setup-entry.ts` - Setup-only entry point

**Configuration Files:**
- `api.ts`, `channel-config-api.ts`, `runtime-api.ts`, `session-key-api.ts`, `test-api.ts`, `test-support.ts`, `update-offset-runtime-api.ts`

**Core Implementation (src/ - 192 files total):**
- `channel.ts` (964 lines) - Main plugin definition
- `channel.test.ts` - Integration tests
- `accounts.ts` - Account resolution and listing
- `setup-core.ts`, `setup-surface.ts` - Setup/onboarding
- `bot/` subdirectory - Telegram bot integration layer
- `send.ts`, `outbound-adapter.ts` - Message delivery
- `monitoring/polling/webhook` - Event ingestion (`monitor.ts`, `polling-session.ts`, `webhook.ts`)
- `probe.ts`, `audit.ts` - Status/capabilities probing
- `approval-native.ts`, `exec-approvals.ts` - Approval system
