## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `package.json`

Mirror `extensions/nostr/package.json`. Key fields:

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "private": true,
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": { "openclaw": "workspace:*" },
  "peerDependencies": { "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1" },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (API Token)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin boards and direct messages via PulseBoard.",
      "order": 75,
      "quickstartAllowFrom": true
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "defaultChoice": "npm",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    }
  }
}
```

Note: **`openclaw.install.npmSpec` must equal `@openclaw/pulseboard`**, matching
the `name` field (repo invariant for bundled plugins).

---

### Step 2 — `openclaw.plugin.json`

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

The `id` must match `openclaw.channel.id` in `package.json`, the directory name,
and the config section key (`channels.pulseboard`).

---

### Step 3 — `src/config-schema.ts`

Define Zod schemas for PulseBoard config using `buildChannelConfigSchema` from
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema`:

- `PulseBoardAccountSchema`: `z.object({ serverUrl, token, displayName?, dmPolicy?, allowFrom?, defaultTo? })`
  - `serverUrl`: `z.string().url()` — base URL of the PulseBoard server
  - `token`: `z.string().min(1)` — API token (mark as secret in setup hints)
  - `displayName`: `z.string().optional()` — human-readable bot name
  - `dmPolicy`: `z.enum(["pairing","allowlist","open","disabled"]).optional()`
  - `allowFrom`: `z.array(z.string()).optional()`
  - `defaultTo`: `z.string().optional()`

- `PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema` = `buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardAccountSchema)`
  (wraps top-level channel config; adds standard `enabled` / metadata)

---

### Step 4 — `src/types.ts`

Define TypeScript types and account-resolution functions:

```typescript
// Raw config shape (mirrors PulseBoardAccountSchema)
export interface PulseBoardAccountConfig { ... }

// Resolved account (computed from config)
export interface ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  configured: boolean;
  serverUrl: string | undefined;
  token: string | undefined;
  displayName: string | undefined;
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
}

// Typed OpenClawConfig with pulseboard channel section
export interface CoreConfig extends OpenClawConfig {
  channels?: { pulseboard?: PulseBoardAccountConfig };
}
```

Implement:
- `listPulseBoardAccountIds(cfg)` → always returns `["default"]` (single-account model)
- `resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId(cfg)` → `"default"`
- `resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId? })` → returns `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`
  with `configured = !!(serverUrl && token)`

